- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is also likely as the paper discusses the effectiveness of key features in making the obfuscation more resilient against SAT attacks. 
- cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) is another possible category as the paper specifically targets FPGA bitstreams and ASIC netlists. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is less likely but still possible as the paper discusses the use of Look-Up-Tables in the proposed obfuscation algorithm. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is unlikely as there is no mention of machine learning in the paper.
